tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  26,138,"And we are not going to be punished."
  26,141,"The Thamūd disbelieved in all the messenger by their rejection of Saleh (peace be upon him)."
  26,144,"“So be mindful of Allah by fulfilling His commandments and refrain from that which He has prohibited. And obey me in whatever I have commanded you with and forbidden you from.”"
  26,147,"In gardens and flowing springs."
  26,150,"“So be mindful of Allah by fulfilling His commandments and refrain from that which He has prohibited. And obey me in whatever I have commanded you with and forbidden you from.”"
  26,151,"“And do not submit to the commands of those who are immoderate on themselves by committing sins.”"
  26,152,"“Those who cause corruption on Earth by spreading sins and do not rectify themselves by holding on to the obedience of Allah.”"